  "texts": [
    "Patchcore then determines whether the test sample is abnormal based on the distance between the test sample′s nearest neighbor feature in its memory bank and other features.",
    "This process of reweighting makes patchcore more robust.",
    "Since patchcore was proposed, numerous improved methods have been developed on its foundation.",
    "Coupled-hypersphere-based feature adaptation (CFA) is proposed by Lee et al. [69] to obtain target-oriented features.",
    "The center and surface of the hypersphere in the memory bank are obtained through transfer learning, and the positional relationship between the test feature and the coupled-hypersphere can be used to determine whether it is abnormal or not."
  ],
